### ClickNBack — Workflow 4: Wallet Summary and Payout
###
### Goal: Check a user's cashback wallet and request a withdrawal (payout).
###       An admin then processes the payout.
### Roles: User (wallet + payout request), Admin (payout processing)
###
### Prerequisites:
###   - A confirmed purchase with cashback > 0 exists for the user
###     (run 03-purchase-and-cashback.http through step 3).
###
### ⚪ STATUS: These endpoints are BACKLOG — fully specified but not yet implemented.
###    This file documents the intended API surface so you can understand the
###    domain model and prepare integration tests ahead of time.
###
### Live API: https://clicknback.com
### Docs:     https://clicknback.com/docs

@baseUrl = https://clicknback.com


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 1 — Login as the user
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name userLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "Alice1234!"
}


###

@userToken = PASTE_USER_TOKEN_HERE
@userId    = PASTE_USER_ID_HERE


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 2 — View wallet summary
#
# Expected: 200 OK with three balance fields:
#   - pending:   cashback earned from confirmed purchases, not yet withdrawable
#   - available: cashback the user can withdraw right now
#   - paid:      total already paid out in past payouts
#
# The sum pending + available represents the user's total unrealised cashback.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{userId}}/wallet
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 3 — List wallet transactions
#
# Expected: a paginated ledger of cashback credits (from purchase confirmations)
# and debits (from payout requests and reversals).
# Each transaction shows: type, amount, status, and a reference to the
# source purchase or payout.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{userId}}/wallet/transactions?page=1&page_size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 4 — Request a payout (withdrawal)
#
# Expected: 201 Created with a payout record in "pending" state.
# Copy the `id` value and set @payoutId below.
#
# Business rules:
#   - amount must be <= available balance
#   - A payout cannot exceed the user's available balance
#   - Funds move to a "processing" state until an admin approves or rejects
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name requestPayout
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{userId}}/payouts
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}

{
  "amount": 5.00
}


###

@payoutId = PASTE_PAYOUT_ID_HERE


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 4b — Verify wallet after payout request
#
# Expected: available balance decreases by the requested amount.
# The funds are now in "processing" state (not yet reflected in "paid").
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{userId}}/wallet
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 5 — Login as admin to process the payout
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# @name adminLogin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "carol@clicknback.com",
  "password": "Str0ng!Pass"
}


###

@adminToken = PASTE_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 6 — List all pending payouts (admin view)
#
# Expected: paginated list of payout requests waiting for processing.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payouts?status=pending&page=1&page_size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 7a — Approve the payout
#
# Expected: 200 OK. Funds move from "processing" to "paid".
# The user's paid balance increases.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payouts/{{payoutId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

{
  "status": "approved"
}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 7b — (Alternative) Reject the payout
#
# Expected: 200 OK. Funds are returned to the user's available balance.
# Use this to simulate a failed or reversed withdrawal.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/payouts/{{payoutId}}/status
# Content-Type: application/json
# Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
#
# {
#   "status": "rejected"
# }


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 8 — Verify wallet balances after payout processing
#
# Expected (after approval):
#   - available: unchanged or 0 if fully withdrawn
#   - paid:      increased by the payout amount
#
# Expected (after rejection):
#   - available: restored to pre-request value
#   - paid:      unchanged
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{userId}}/wallet
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}


###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# USER VIEW — List the user's own payout history
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{userId}}/payouts?page=1&page_size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
